    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Offshoring Prevention Act</strong> </p> <p> This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to include imported property income in foreign base company income, for purposes of determining the income of controlled foreign corporations. </p> <p>The bill defines "imported property income" as, with certain exceptions, income derived in connection with:</p> <ul> <li>manufacturing, producing, growing, or extracting imported property;</li> <li> the sale, exchange, or other disposition of imported property; or</li> <li>the lease, rental, or licensing of imported property.</li> </ul> <p>The bill also provides for a separate application of limitations on the foreign tax credit for imported property income.</p>]]></text>
